30:14.821 --> 30:16.643
I've had enough bad news for one day.

30:16.645 --> 30:18.425
Too damn bad. I'm coming in.

30:19.626 --> 30:22.193
Wow, look at all the happy faces.

30:23.964 --> 30:25.897
You come up with something
to refute the charges

30:25.899 --> 30:27.499
that George committed credit card fraud?

30:27.501 --> 30:28.867
Although, for the life of me,

30:28.869 --> 30:31.202
I still don't see
what that has to do with this.

30:31.204 --> 30:32.637
Cable's working on it.

30:32.639 --> 30:34.539
I've been watching the
closed circuit security tapes

30:34.541 --> 30:37.208
of the robbery that came
over with the prosecution's

30:37.210 --> 30:39.511
latest batch of discovery materials.

30:39.513 --> 30:41.513
Can I show you guys something?

30:41.515 --> 30:43.181
There's no sound.

30:43.183 --> 30:45.494
Just picture.
So you got to watch carefully.

30:47.020 --> 30:50.188
Okay, see what George's brother
does after everything is done?

30:50.190 --> 30:51.589
He's got the money.

30:51.591 --> 30:53.473
Now, based on the time stamp,
we know that,

30:53.475 --> 30:54.915
by this time, the alarm is going off.

30:54.917 --> 30:57.328
So he's got to be concerned
that the cops are on their way.

30:57.330 --> 30:58.630
Watch him.

30:58.632 --> 31:02.233
He starts to head out,
and then he comes back.

31:02.235 --> 31:03.983
Looks like he's saying something.

31:03.985 --> 31:06.431
He's realizing something's wrong.

31:07.541 --> 31:09.741
See?

31:09.743 --> 31:11.075
He's realizing

31:11.077 --> 31:12.810
his friend is dead.

31:12.812 --> 31:14.946
When's the last time
you heard about a robber

31:14.948 --> 31:17.348
stopping midgetaway
to check his victim's pulse?

31:17.350 --> 31:19.817
So you think if we show this to a jury

31:19.819 --> 31:21.686
after we put Rick on the stand,
they'll believe

31:21.688 --> 31:23.888
that Kirk's death was accidental?

31:23.890 --> 31:25.290
Yes!

31:26.126 --> 31:28.241
I think George has an alibi.

31:28.243 --> 31:30.261
Well, what do you mean?

31:30.263 --> 31:31.930
Okay, on the day of the purchase,

31:31.932 --> 31:33.002
he was nowhere near New Hampshire.

31:33.004 --> 31:36.050
He was working as a dishwasher
in a restaurant he now owns.

31:36.052 --> 31:38.349
I just finished reaching out
to his old boss, the man

31:38.351 --> 31:39.804
he bought the restaurant from.

31:39.806 --> 31:41.573
He has time cards and eyewitnesses.

31:41.575 --> 31:43.775
There is no way he could have done it.

31:43.777 --> 31:45.299
What do you think?

31:45.301 --> 31:46.638
It's good.

31:47.214 --> 31:50.215
I just wish it was a little more.

31:50.217 --> 31:52.884
And I wish with all my heart
it proved he had no idea

31:52.886 --> 31:54.726
what his brother and best friend
were up to that night.

31:54.728 --> 31:57.827
Well, actually,
there is a little bit more.

31:57.828 --> 31:59.460
I tracked down the Best Buy receipts

31:59.462 --> 32:01.429
and located all the serial
numbers and identifiers

32:01.431 --> 32:02.964
associated with the purchased items,

32:02.966 --> 32:04.899
which were actually laptops, by the way.

32:04.901 --> 32:07.035
Then I did a search for those.

32:07.037 --> 32:08.670
And after all this time,
I actually found one

32:08.672 --> 32:09.704
on an archived

32:09.706 --> 32:11.239
online auction site.

32:11.241 --> 32:12.874
I did a little hacking

32:12.876 --> 32:15.910
and tracked down the seller's IP address.

32:15.912 --> 32:16.945
And it turns out

32:16.947 --> 32:20.114
it belongs to an Emory Cochburn,

32:20.116 --> 32:24.018
who, by the way, is in prison
for insurance fraud.

32:24.020 --> 32:26.254
- Which means...?
- Which means

32:26.256 --> 32:29.390
whoever sold the stolen
Social Security number to George

32:29.392 --> 32:31.357
sold it at least one more time.

32:31.359 --> 32:33.127
Looks that way.

32:33.129 --> 32:34.429
Nice work, Cable.

32:34.431 --> 32:36.130
I just wish

32:36.132 --> 32:37.398
it cleared George of the crime

32:37.400 --> 32:39.634
we were hired to defend him from.

32:39.636 --> 32:41.502
George Brown stole
the Social Security number

32:41.504 --> 32:42.904
of the deceased, Jim Grayson,

32:42.906 --> 32:44.739
to establish a new identity.

32:44.741 --> 32:46.407
He then opened a credit card

32:46.409 --> 32:48.476
at a Best Buy
in Manchester, New Hampshire,

32:48.478 --> 32:51.813
and used that card to purchase
$10,000 worth of electronics

32:51.815 --> 32:53.615
that he had no intention
of ever paying for.

32:54.498 --> 32:56.818
Thank you, Officer Lyden.

33:01.725 --> 33:03.725
Officer Lyden, thank you.

33:03.727 --> 33:05.560
Thank you for taking the time and coming

33:05.562 --> 33:07.462
- to talk to us today.
- My pleasure.

33:07.464 --> 33:08.930
Let me ask you something.

33:08.932 --> 33:11.766
Do you have any actual proof

33:11.768 --> 33:17.272
that the man sitting before you
here today is the same man

33:17.274 --> 33:19.374
who fraudulently applied
for a credit card

33:19.376 --> 33:21.075
and bought these electronics?

33:21.077 --> 33:25.446
Of course. It's the same name,
same Social Security number.

33:25.448 --> 33:27.115
What else do you need?

33:27.117 --> 33:29.183
And what if I told you
that this Jim Grayson,

33:29.185 --> 33:32.954
also known as George Brown,
was in Glen Rock, New Jersey,

33:32.956 --> 33:35.123
hundreds of miles away
at the time of the purchase,

33:35.125 --> 33:36.791
and that someone else had bought

33:36.793 --> 33:39.394
the same stolen Social Security number

33:39.396 --> 33:42.130
and committed the theft that you
are attributing to my client?

33:42.132 --> 33:45.033
Well, I would say that sounds
like a pretty convenient story.

33:47.971 --> 33:51.372
Your Honor, we'd like to offer proof

33:51.374 --> 33:53.675
of my client's alibi

33:53.677 --> 33:56.744
in the form of time cards

33:56.746 --> 33:58.980
and eyewitness accounts

33:58.982 --> 34:01.249
from Mr. Brown's place of employment

34:01.251 --> 34:02.817
at the date in question.

34:02.819 --> 34:06.120
It may not be the
slam dunk we need... not yet...

34:06.122 --> 34:07.889
but these jurors are starting to warm up.

34:07.891 --> 34:09.223
I can feel it.

34:09.225 --> 34:10.925
The jury hasn't heard enough to acquit,

34:10.927 --> 34:12.159
or even force a mistrial,

34:12.161 --> 34:13.828
but they're listening to us again.

34:13.830 --> 34:15.563
They think we have something to say,

34:15.565 --> 34:17.264
and I'll take that any time.

34:17.266 --> 34:21.710
Tell Cable thanks for all the hard work.

34:30.215 --> 34:31.614
I just kept thinking
about what you told us

34:31.616 --> 34:32.782
the older brother said.

34:32.784 --> 34:34.967
That this whole thing
was really an inside job.

34:34.969 --> 34:37.405
That no one was supposed
to lose their lives.

34:37.429 --> 34:38.862
That these guys knew each other.

34:38.864 --> 34:41.264
And then I kept thinking
about what you said.

34:41.266 --> 34:44.368
That Rick can testify to it,
but who's gonna believe him?

34:44.370 --> 34:45.502
How do you prove it?

34:45.504 --> 34:47.071
Yeah? So?

34:47.072 --> 34:49.606
So I woke up and watched the tape again.

34:49.608 --> 34:52.141
I mean, the idea of it
actually woke me up.

34:52.949 --> 34:56.746
Only this time, I watched
it with that in mind.

34:57.329 --> 34:59.683
And I think I found something.

35:02.125 --> 35:03.387
See that?

35:03.389 --> 35:04.961
See what?

35:05.858 --> 35:08.859
Kirk, the friend, he puts his hands up

35:08.861 --> 35:11.462
before Rick pulls out his gun.

35:13.499 --> 35:16.600
You want proof it was an
inside job, there it is.

35:17.224 --> 35:19.336
You want to prove that
they knew each other,

35:19.338 --> 35:21.105
there it is.

35:21.107 --> 35:23.874
You want to prove that no one
was supposed to die that night?

35:23.876 --> 35:25.676
Picture's worth a thousand words.

35:25.678 --> 35:28.312
If we can prove it's an inside
job with the cooperation

35:28.314 --> 35:29.746
of an employee of the store,

35:29.748 --> 35:31.148
technically, there's no armed robbery,

35:31.150 --> 35:34.284
which negates the felony murder
charge, which means...

35:34.286 --> 35:36.787
George is actually innocent.

35:42.795 --> 35:44.661
Well, what'd you get?

35:44.663 --> 35:46.630
The mother lode, pretty much.

35:46.632 --> 35:48.196
Although I think I did promise

35:48.198 --> 35:50.153
- to marry the guy who got them for me.
- Excellent.

35:50.155 --> 35:51.602
Who doesn't love a good wedding?

35:51.604 --> 35:52.903
So you're looking at call logs

35:52.905 --> 35:54.404
between Kirk's pager and Rick's phone,

35:54.406 --> 35:56.406
Rick's pager and Kirk's phone,

35:56.408 --> 35:59.076
and calls between both men's
phones starting in late 1999.

35:59.078 --> 36:02.212
Then it jumps to ten exchanges per day

36:02.214 --> 36:04.813
during the week of the robbery.

36:05.484 --> 36:07.217
Great.

36:07.219 --> 36:09.520
Um, go home, get some sleep.

36:10.709 --> 36:12.933
What is your relationship
to the defendant?

36:14.364 --> 36:16.725
He's my younger brother.

36:16.727 --> 36:18.529
And what was your relationship

36:18.531 --> 36:20.430
to the clerk who died in the robbery...

36:20.432 --> 36:22.032
Kirk Getty?

36:22.034 --> 36:26.470
I worked in the mall as a custodian.

36:26.472 --> 36:28.338
Kirk sold sunglasses.

36:28.340 --> 36:30.140
We met one night.

36:30.142 --> 36:32.172
We hit it off.

36:32.174 --> 36:34.778
We realized, we had a lot in common.

36:34.780 --> 36:36.246
So,

36:36.248 --> 36:38.916
I mean, at what point
did the two of you decide

36:38.918 --> 36:40.609
to stage a robbery together?

36:40.611 --> 36:42.243
Objection. Leading.

36:43.739 --> 36:44.988
My apologies, Your Honor.

36:44.990 --> 36:46.690
Let me word it a different way.

36:46.692 --> 36:50.227
Whose idea was it

36:50.229 --> 36:52.696
to rob a check cashing place?

36:52.698 --> 36:56.700
Well, it actually started out
with Kirk. He...

36:56.702 --> 36:59.136
You know, he wanted
to buy this motorcycle.

36:59.138 --> 37:02.839
But truthfully, within 90 seconds,

37:02.841 --> 37:04.241
we were planning it together.

37:04.243 --> 37:07.745
Because he worked there,
he knew all the important stuff,

37:07.747 --> 37:10.013
like combination to the safe

37:10.015 --> 37:12.282
and what day and time to show up

37:12.284 --> 37:14.716
when there would be the most cash there.

37:15.521 --> 37:18.411
It really seemed like
it was gonna be easy.

37:18.413 --> 37:20.357
Andand what about
your brother, George Brown?

37:20.359 --> 37:21.592
Was he in on the planning?

37:21.594 --> 37:25.162
No. George would never do
something like that.

37:25.164 --> 37:28.065
All he was doing that night
was picking me up from work.

37:29.105 --> 37:30.801
He didn't know why I wanted

37:30.803 --> 37:32.936
to stop by the check cashing place.

37:32.938 --> 37:35.105
All he wanted was to get home.

37:35.107 --> 37:37.040
So you never planned on killing anyone?

37:37.042 --> 37:39.813
Of course not. There were
no bullets in the gun.

37:40.320 --> 37:42.746
It was all for the security camera.

37:42.748 --> 37:46.183
With that in mind,
we'd like to enter into evidence

37:46.185 --> 37:48.952
the security camera
footage from that night,

37:48.954 --> 37:51.989
with a particular emphasis
on the time code numbers

37:51.991 --> 37:55.125
indicated on the paperwork.

37:56.216 --> 37:59.446
You can clearly see the victim
with his hands up,

37:59.448 --> 38:02.733
even before the witness
exposes his weapon.

38:02.735 --> 38:04.501
A clear indication that he knew exactly

38:04.503 --> 38:06.470
what was going to happen that night.

38:07.573 --> 38:09.506
As well as another time code,

38:09.508 --> 38:11.975
which clearly shows
the witness delaying his exit

38:11.977 --> 38:13.510
out of the store,

38:13.512 --> 38:16.046
so he could check
on the condition of his friend

38:16.048 --> 38:19.783
once he realized that he was
in some form of distress.

38:19.785 --> 38:24.450
Additionally, we'd like to enter
into evidence phone records

38:24.452 --> 38:28.225
that clearly indicate
the prior relationship

38:28.227 --> 38:30.260
between the witness and the victim.

38:32.665 --> 38:34.264
Order in the court, please.

38:34.266 --> 38:38.368
Let's quiet down. Let's quiet down.

38:38.370 --> 38:40.837
No further questions
for this witness, Your Honor.

38:42.846 --> 38:45.509
Marissa, we just hit them with
all the firepower we've got.

38:45.511 --> 38:46.843
Tell me it made a difference.

38:46.845 --> 38:49.346
You want the good news or the bad news?

38:49.348 --> 38:51.081
All your generative jurors
finally woke up

38:51.083 --> 38:52.549
and have gone green.

38:52.551 --> 38:54.918
Bad news is, there's only six of them.

38:54.920 --> 38:57.587
The other six aren't quite there yet.

38:57.589 --> 38:59.690
Mr. Peluso, your witness.

38:59.692 --> 39:03.694
In light of all this new information,

39:03.696 --> 39:05.996
if it pleases the Court, I was hoping

39:05.998 --> 39:07.898
I could request a brief recess?

39:07.900 --> 39:11.368
This court will take a 20minute recess.

39:12.417 --> 39:14.137
What do you think that means?

39:14.139 --> 39:16.373
I don't know. Maybe he's a smoker.

39:16.375 --> 39:17.908
Maybe he's got a small bladder.

39:21.551 --> 39:23.361
Maybe he wants to borrow some money.

39:23.363 --> 39:24.748
I'll be right back.

39:28.850 --> 39:30.587
It's a great system, isn't it?

39:31.311 --> 39:34.491
You go into it thinking,
â€œI know what's going on here.

39:34.493 --> 39:36.215
â€œI know what's right.

39:36.897 --> 39:38.195
I know where this is gonna end upâ€...

39:38.197 --> 39:39.763
And then...

39:39.765 --> 39:41.965
It's just a great system.

39:42.280 --> 39:45.435
I think it's, like,
sevenfive, or fiveseven.

39:45.437 --> 39:47.070
Or maybe it's split down the middle.

39:47.072 --> 39:49.740
- What do you think?
- I think he's an innocent man.

39:49.742 --> 39:53.243
I think you know it.
I think they feel it.

39:53.245 --> 39:55.946
Thing is, you're not gonna get
'em all, and neither am I,

39:55.948 --> 39:57.581
which means you're staring at a mistrial,

39:57.583 --> 40:00.375
which means you steal another year

40:00.377 --> 40:02.586
of this guy's life while he sits in jail

40:02.588 --> 40:04.287
waiting for his second day in court.

40:04.289 --> 40:06.757
And his kids keep growing,
and his wife keeps wondering

40:06.759 --> 40:08.658
why she suddenly became a single parent.

40:08.660 --> 40:11.094
And he's forced to close his business

40:11.096 --> 40:12.596
and let his employees go.

40:12.598 --> 40:16.064
And like I said when we
first met, what's the point?

40:17.202 --> 40:18.702
He's not a criminal.

40:18.704 --> 40:20.337
He never was.

40:20.339 --> 40:23.607
You really want me to go in
there and ask for a dismissal?

40:24.155 --> 40:25.675
I have people I have to answer to.

40:25.677 --> 40:27.811
This is not an easy conversation to have.

40:27.813 --> 40:30.013
Yeah, but the conversation
you want to have

40:30.015 --> 40:33.583
isn't happening today, so why
not get this one over with?

40:33.585 --> 40:36.453
In fact, why don't you
call 'em right now?

40:37.168 --> 40:39.589
Mr. Assistant District Attorney,
you're not a stupid man.

40:39.591 --> 40:42.192
You know you're not getting a
conviction against George Brown.

40:42.194 --> 40:43.960
Not today, not ever.

40:43.962 --> 40:46.797
And that's with me and my team
having about a week to prepare.

40:46.799 --> 40:50.901
You put my client through
another year of this hell,

40:50.903 --> 40:54.471
and I promise you I will
spend every day of that year

40:54.473 --> 40:56.773
getting ready for the new trial.

40:57.438 --> 41:00.410
And when we meet again,
you won't know what hit you.

41:01.359 --> 41:05.048
Now I'm gonna go back inside
while you make up your mind.

41:05.822 --> 41:07.284
Surprise me.

41:16.669 --> 41:17.946
Your Honor?

41:18.788 --> 41:21.431
It's a great system, isn't it?

41:22.667 --> 41:25.735
You go into a trial thinking,
â€œI know what's going on here.

41:25.760 --> 41:26.993
â€œI know what's right.

41:27.039 --> 41:29.139
I know where this is gonna end up.â€

41:29.141 --> 41:31.007
And then the system humbles you.

41:31.556 --> 41:33.677
You realize you hadn't
considered all the facts,

41:33.679 --> 41:36.046
that your thinking may have been flawed.

41:36.048 --> 41:39.850
And that incarcerating someone
who almost certainly had no idea

41:39.852 --> 41:42.319
what was going on
in a building 35 feet away

41:42.321 --> 41:44.554
while he sat in a car makes no sense.

41:44.556 --> 41:46.790
I believe that's the case here.

41:46.792 --> 41:49.025
And with that in mind,
the district attorney's office

41:49.027 --> 41:50.694
would like to enter a motion

41:50.696 --> 41:53.296
to dismiss all charges
against George Brown.

41:54.700 --> 41:57.033
This court will accept
the prosecution's motion.

41:57.035 --> 41:58.468
The defendant is free to go.

41:58.470 --> 42:00.904
And we thank the jury for its service.

42:06.411 --> 42:08.645
Thank you.

42:17.560 --> 42:19.656
I know we've never met before.

42:21.527 --> 42:24.528
But my name is George.

42:24.530 --> 42:26.696
My last name is Brown.

42:28.667 --> 42:31.268
And you'd make me
the happiest man in the world

42:31.270 --> 42:34.938
if you'd marry me and make that
your last name, too.

42:44.683 --> 42:48.383
You know, I think those two
have a future together.

42:49.634 --> 42:51.121
Wait a second.

42:51.552 --> 42:54.391
Are those tears? You
crying, you big old softie?

42:54.393 --> 42:56.493
Excuse me. I believe you're mistaken.

42:56.495 --> 42:58.695
These are not tears.

42:58.697 --> 43:00.730
Wasn't it Tom Hanks who famously said,

43:00.732 --> 43:03.533
There's no tears in trial science?

43:03.535 --> 43:05.869
No. I believe he was talking
about chocolates.

43:05.871 --> 43:08.805
- No reference to trial science.
- Whatever.

